786
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:54,760
 And our dating should be the same.

787
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:57,420
 That's what people want.

788
00:32:57,420 --> 00:32:58,700
 According to one of the largest surveys

789
00:32:58,700 --> 00:33:00,500
 conducted on singles and dating in America

790
00:33:00,500 --> 00:33:02,340
 from people just like you,

791
00:33:02,340 --> 00:33:05,440
 the highest value in a potential partner

792
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:09,400
 is someone who is upfront about their relationship goals.

793
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:12,520
 Meaning we don't want to play games with each other.

794
00:33:12,520 --> 00:33:16,220
 We want to speak plain to each other.

795
00:33:16,220 --> 00:33:17,720
 We want to say what we mean,

796
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:19,900
 and we want to mean what we say.

797
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:21,900
 I remember when Brooke and I were dating

798
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:24,740
 early on in our relationship.

799
00:33:24,740 --> 00:33:26,460
 We went on a date, amazing date,

800
00:33:26,460 --> 00:33:27,700
 planned the entire thing out,

801
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:29,100
 had an incredible evening together,

802
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:30,540
 stimulating conversation.

803
00:33:30,540 --> 00:33:33,300
 And I drove to drop her off at the Southern Dormitories

804
00:33:33,300 --> 00:33:34,180
 at Texas A&M University.

805
00:33:34,180 --> 00:33:37,080
 Do not whoop for the sake of our other friends in the room.

806
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,180
 Though I love you.

807
00:33:39,180 --> 00:33:43,480
 And I leaned in, unplanned, and I kissed her goodnight.

808
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:47,540
 It did not take long, less than 24 hours,

809
00:33:47,540 --> 00:33:49,740
 for her to call me and say,

810
00:33:49,740 --> 00:33:51,660
 "We need to process some things."

811
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:53,740
 So we sat in my truck the next day,

812
00:33:53,740 --> 00:33:55,100
 and she looked at me and she said,

813
00:33:55,100 --> 00:33:57,020
 "I don't know what kind of girl you think I am,

814
00:33:57,020 --> 00:33:59,760
 "but that's not the kind of girl that I actually am.

815
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:03,240
 "I am not okay with that line of engagement.

816
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:05,020
 "That's confusing to me.

817
00:34:05,020 --> 00:34:07,100
 "What do you actually want this to be?"

818
00:34:07,100 --> 00:34:09,380
 And it was there in the truck

819
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:11,020
 that I defined our relationship,

820
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:12,740
 because she called me to the carpet,

821
00:34:12,740 --> 00:34:14,060
 and I loved her for it.

822
00:34:14,060 --> 00:34:15,460
 Ladies, this isn't even in my notes,

823
00:34:15,460 --> 00:34:17,180
 but I just need you to know for me,

824
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:20,980
 so much of the maturity of our men hinges upon

825
00:34:20,980 --> 00:34:22,660
 your ability to look at them and say,

826
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:25,220
 "I'm not putting up with this."

827
00:34:25,220 --> 00:34:27,580
 They will do as I did.

828
00:34:27,580 --> 00:34:30,820
 They will lay restless at night in their bed,

829
00:34:30,820 --> 00:34:34,740
 and they will wonder, "What has happened to me?"

830
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:38,000
 And you actually have the key

831
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:40,340
 to unlocking their growth in God.

832
00:34:40,340 --> 00:34:44,460
 We must be clear with one another,

833
00:34:44,460 --> 00:34:46,860
 which means we don't flirt with someone

834
00:34:46,860 --> 00:34:48,580
 just to get a sense of validation.

835
00:34:48,580 --> 00:34:51,580
 I talk to guys, and I've literally heard guys

836
00:34:51,580 --> 00:34:53,060
 look at me and say, "But I love the thrill

837
00:34:53,060 --> 00:34:54,060
 "of the hunt, Kylan."

838
00:34:54,060 --> 00:34:56,100
 Do you know how weird that sounds?

839
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:57,100
 (audience laughing)

840
00:34:57,100 --> 00:34:59,660
 Like, take the camouflage off, bro.

841
00:34:59,660 --> 00:35:01,940
 Like, she's not a trophy for you to hunt and kill.

842
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:04,820
 She is a treasure for you to find and keep.

843
00:35:04,820 --> 00:35:07,260
 Like, you're not gonna mount her on your wall.

844
00:35:07,260 --> 00:35:09,780
 You're gonna move in together,

845
00:35:09,780 --> 00:35:11,260
 and you're going to serve one another.

846
00:35:11,260 --> 00:35:12,500
 That's the nature of how this goes.

847
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:13,860
 Ladies, stop hiding behind the excuse

848
00:35:13,860 --> 00:35:15,500
 that you're just bubbly, and you can't help the fact

849
00:35:15,500 --> 00:35:17,940
 that he's catching the wrong idea.

850
00:35:20,300 --> 00:35:22,780
 Avoid emotionally charged friendships.

851
00:35:22,780 --> 00:35:24,460
 Like, don't have full conversations through text

852
00:35:24,460 --> 00:35:26,780
 or spend multiple hours a week with that girl or that guy

853
00:35:26,780 --> 00:35:29,940
 who you have absolutely no legitimate interest in.

854
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:31,540
 Even if you love spending time with them,

855
00:35:31,540 --> 00:35:32,420
 here's the thing.

856
00:35:32,420 --> 00:35:34,960
 If you love spending time with them, then date them.

857
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,260
 But the reality is, many of you don't love

858
00:35:36,260 --> 00:35:37,100
 spending time with them.

859
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:39,240
 You love that they're spending time with you.

860
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:43,020
 And that's very validating, and yet it's very confusing.

861
00:35:43,020 --> 00:35:44,900
 Stop ghosting them.

862
00:35:44,900 --> 00:35:46,780
 Do I actually need to unpack this one?

863
00:35:46,780 --> 00:35:49,980
 Here's what I would say.

864
00:35:49,980 --> 00:35:53,060
 If you're not interested, affirm them where you can

865
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:55,940
 and graciously tell them you just don't see it

866
00:35:55,940 --> 00:35:56,840
 working out for yourself.

867
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:58,300
 I will literally tell you what to say.

868
00:35:58,300 --> 00:35:59,140
 Are you listening?

869
00:35:59,140 --> 00:35:59,960
 Here's what you can say.

870
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:01,420
 If you're not interested in someone, you can say,

871
00:36:01,420 --> 00:36:04,160
 "Hey, I think you're great,

872
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:06,780
 "but I don't think we're a great fit.

873
00:36:06,780 --> 00:36:08,860
 "Thank you for the honor of asking me out."

874
00:36:08,860 --> 00:36:10,740
 That's it.

875
00:36:10,740 --> 00:36:12,180
 It's that simple.

876
00:36:12,180 --> 00:36:17,100
 It's dignifying to the other person, not demeaning to them.

877
00:36:17,100 --> 00:36:19,840
 You actually treat them like they exist,

878
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,520
 that they're a child of God,

879
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:23,900
 that they're your brother or sister in Christ.

880
00:36:23,900 --> 00:36:26,500
 You don't ghost them.

881
00:36:26,500 --> 00:36:31,220
 Avoid using some derivative of, "It's not you, it's me."

882
00:36:31,220 --> 00:36:33,780
 No, it is them.

883
00:36:33,780 --> 00:36:34,940
 So tell them that.

884
00:36:34,940 --> 00:36:36,060
 (congregation laughing)

885
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:39,220
 Saying things like, "I'll always love you.

886
00:36:39,220 --> 00:36:40,060
 "You're so great.

887
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:41,940
 "Maybe one day the timing's just bad."

888
00:36:41,940 --> 00:36:43,340
 That is not helping them.

889
00:36:43,340 --> 00:36:44,160
 Listen to me.

890
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:46,600
 Clarity brings closure,

891
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:50,460
 and it's kindness to help people close the chapter

892
00:36:50,460 --> 00:36:51,740
 on one stage of life

893
00:36:51,740 --> 00:36:54,220
 so they might begin to write a new chapter with someone else.

894
00:36:54,220 --> 00:36:55,840
 You do that for them.

895
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,820
 I'm not saying you cut them down to the knees.

896
00:36:57,820 --> 00:36:59,160
 "Well, I hate you because you smell bad,

897
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,000
 "and your hair's weird,

898
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,980
 "and you have a weird taste in food or music."

899
00:37:01,980 --> 00:37:03,560
 Don't do that.

900
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:04,820
 Be clear with them.

901
00:37:04,820 --> 00:37:06,640
 Gracious, but truthful.

902
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:08,620
 And then definitely, last but not least,

903
00:37:08,620 --> 00:37:10,540
 quit using God as your excuse.

904
00:37:10,540 --> 00:37:14,500
 (congregation cheering)

905
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:16,900
 It is insincere

906
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:19,680
 to say

907
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:26,920
 that God is calling you someplace else,

908
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:29,240
 that you just don't have peace about this,

909
00:37:29,240 --> 00:37:32,560
 that you're still processing with your community

910
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:34,940
 when in reality, you just don't like them.

911
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:36,820
 Listen to me.

912
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:38,140
 I'm not trying to be funny.

913
00:37:38,140 --> 00:37:39,560
 I'm really wanting to engage with you

914
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:42,160
 because this sounds nice,

915
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:45,440
 but what it does is it excuses you from the responsibility,

916
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:48,460
 and it accuses God of being at fault.

917
00:37:48,460 --> 00:37:49,740
 Do not do that.

918
00:37:49,740 --> 00:37:52,280
 Do not call his character into question

919
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:54,120
 in the life of another believer

920
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:55,880
 because you're not interested.

921
00:37:55,880 --> 00:38:00,240
 That is a disproportionate allocation of value.

922
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:03,480
 It's okay to say, "I don't see this working,"

923
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:06,640
 but don't tell them God doesn't see it working.

924
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:07,880
 Proverbs 24, 26 says,

925
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:11,460
 "An honest answer is like a kiss on the lips.

926
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:14,000
 "Clarity is kindness, so be clear with one another."

927
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:18,480
 And lastly for tonight, don't be dramatic.

928
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:22,600
 Do be steady.

929
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:24,960
 You be steady.

930
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,140
 Second Corinthians 10, five says,

931
00:38:26,140 --> 00:38:28,200
 "We destroy arguments and every lofty opinion

932
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:29,720
 "raised against the knowledge of God,

933
00:38:29,720 --> 00:38:32,440
 "and we take every thought captive to obey Christ."

934
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:33,540
 Isaiah 26, three says,

935
00:38:33,540 --> 00:38:34,920
 "You keep him in perfect peace,

936
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:38,480
 "whose mind is stayed on you because he trusts in you."

937
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:39,320
 Philippians 4, eight says,

938
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:40,900
 "Finally, brothers and sisters,

939
00:38:40,900 --> 00:38:42,660
 "whatever is true and honorable and just

940
00:38:42,660 --> 00:38:44,420
 "and pure and lovely and commendable,

941
00:38:44,420 --> 00:38:45,560
 "if there's any excellence,

942
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:47,020
 "if there's anything worthy of praise,

943
00:38:47,020 --> 00:38:49,400
 "then think about these things."

944
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:53,120
 You hear what these verses are emphasizing?

945
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:55,360
 They are all emphasizing your thought life,

946
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:57,640
 that we should take thoughts captive to obey Christ,

947
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:59,120
 that we should keep our minds stayed on God,

948
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,400
 that we should think about godly things.

949
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:01,360
 Why does that matter?

950
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:05,120
 Because you want to date someone that's in their right mind.

951
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:06,320
 I remember a mentor of mine,

952
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:07,480
 he called me and he asked me,

953
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,800
 "Hey, how are you and Brooke doing?"

954
00:39:08,800 --> 00:39:11,320
 And I responded, "Man, we're doing really great.

955
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:13,660
 "Like nothing really new to report."

956
00:39:13,660 --> 00:39:14,660
 And I loved his response.

957
00:39:14,660 --> 00:39:17,560
 He sighed on the other end of the phone and he said,

958
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:19,260
 "Man, isn't that awesome?"

959
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:26,020
 Steadiness is not listed amongst the most sexy qualities

960
00:39:26,020 --> 00:39:27,420
 to find in a suitor,

961
00:39:27,420 --> 00:39:29,260
 but it is listed among the best qualities

962
00:39:29,260 --> 00:39:30,900
 to find in a suitor.

963
00:39:30,900 --> 00:39:33,540
 You want someone that is like their God,

964
00:39:33,540 --> 00:39:36,180
 the same today, yesterday, and forever.

965
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:38,320
 You want them to be consistent.

966
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:40,500
 You don't want to date crazy.

967
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:42,460
 You don't want someone that's lost in their feelings.

968
00:39:42,460 --> 00:39:45,380
 You want someone that's tethered to the truth,

969
00:39:45,380 --> 00:39:49,300
 that tunes their life to the voice of God.

970
00:39:49,300 --> 00:39:50,740
 But Kylan, what about following your heart?

971
00:39:50,740 --> 00:39:53,300
 That is terrible advice.

972
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:55,140
 Do not follow your heart.

973
00:39:55,140 --> 00:39:56,900
 Follow God's word.

974
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:58,940
 Like the scriptures tell us in Proverbs 28, 26,

975
00:39:58,940 --> 00:40:00,420
 as one example,

976
00:40:00,420 --> 00:40:03,520
 he who trusts in his own heart is a fool,

977
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:05,680
 but he who walks wisely will be delivered.

978
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:07,300
 How do you walk wisely

979
00:40:07,300 --> 00:40:09,340
 with the one that has written wisdom

980
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:11,620
 into the fabric of creation?

981
00:40:11,620 --> 00:40:13,980
 You see, the heart wants for things that it should not,

982
00:40:13,980 --> 00:40:16,000
 and it leads us to do things we regret.

983
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:18,360
 So we don't follow our feelings.

984
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:19,600
 We focus on the truth.

985
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,440
 That's who we are.

986
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:21,720
 We are a people of the truth.

987
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:23,580
 We follow it and it alone.

988
00:40:23,580 --> 00:40:25,020
 You see, what you have to know

989
00:40:25,020 --> 00:40:26,340
 is whatever is consistently true

990
00:40:26,340 --> 00:40:28,540
 in your significant other's life

991
00:40:28,540 --> 00:40:31,300
 is going to eventually become consistently true

992
00:40:31,300 --> 00:40:32,900
 in your own life.

993
00:40:32,900 --> 00:40:35,100
 Because as you date and you come together,

994
00:40:35,100 --> 00:40:37,580
 one another, standing in the altar,

995
00:40:37,580 --> 00:40:39,420
 because that's the point and purpose of dating,

996
00:40:39,420 --> 00:40:41,260
 it's to eventually have a series of yeses

997
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:42,740
 that leads to an eventual I do,

998
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:46,060
 what you will find is that what's true of them

999
00:40:46,060 --> 00:40:47,380
 will become true of you.

1000
00:40:47,380 --> 00:40:50,020
 You will become like one another,

1001
00:40:50,020 --> 00:40:52,460
 or you'll just see that this isn't working,

1002
00:40:52,460 --> 00:40:54,660
 and you'll go against God's will and you'll divorce.

1003
00:40:54,660 --> 00:40:56,220
 This is how these things happen.

1004
00:40:56,220 --> 00:40:57,740
 You want someone that is not drama.

1005
00:40:57,740 --> 00:40:58,580
 Well, he's always angry.

1006
00:40:58,580 --> 00:40:59,920
 He can't seem to regulate his emotions.

1007
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,580
 Well, she always knows what's going on with her friends

1008
00:41:01,580 --> 00:41:04,560
 or with her friends or our neighbors' lives.

1009
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:06,500
 Do you think you want someone to know the details

1010
00:41:06,500 --> 00:41:08,340
 of everybody's life as well as the details of yours?

1011
00:41:08,340 --> 00:41:09,180
 It sounds like they're not good

1012
00:41:09,180 --> 00:41:11,860
 at probably keeping that information locked.

1013
00:41:11,860 --> 00:41:12,780
 Well, she likes bad boys.

1014
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:14,740
 That sounds like sabotage to your peace.

1015
00:41:14,740 --> 00:41:17,020
 You know, I would avoid that at all costs.

1016
00:41:17,020 --> 00:41:20,300
 Like you don't want someone that's full of drama.

1017
00:41:20,300 --> 00:41:22,540
 You want someone that's steady.

1018
00:41:22,540 --> 00:41:28,760
 In the book of Judges, we meet a guy by the name of Samson.

1019
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:31,820
 Samson is head over heels in love

1020
00:41:31,820 --> 00:41:33,140
 with this woman named Delilah.

1021
00:41:33,140 --> 00:41:34,700
 She was a Philistine woman.

1022
00:41:34,700 --> 00:41:37,200
 And what you see is there are two things

1023
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:38,980
 characterized in her relationship with Samson.

1024
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:42,100
 She is characterized by a desire for him,

1025
00:41:42,100 --> 00:41:44,860
 but also a deceit of him.

1026
00:41:44,860 --> 00:41:46,660
 You see, she wanted to betray Samson

1027
00:41:46,660 --> 00:41:49,820
 into the hands of her people so they might overcome him.

1028
00:41:49,820 --> 00:41:52,260
 And so the entirety of their relationship,

1029
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:54,460
 she is trying to figure out what his weakness is.

1030
00:41:54,460 --> 00:41:57,420
 You want to know what Samson's weakness was?

1031
00:41:57,420 --> 00:41:59,780
 It wasn't his hair.

1032
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:02,700
 It's that he fell in love with crazy.

1033
00:42:02,700 --> 00:42:04,580
 That's Samson's problem.

1034
00:42:04,580 --> 00:42:07,420
 He started dating drama.

1035
00:42:07,420 --> 00:42:09,700
 Do not make the same mistake.

1036
00:42:09,700 --> 00:42:11,820
 You date to find a spouse.

1037
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:14,220
 You went to find someone that you can link up with

1038
00:42:14,220 --> 00:42:17,140
 and you can move forward through life together alongside.

1039
00:42:17,140 --> 00:42:21,500
 Will you know if they're the one on the first date?

1040
00:42:21,500 --> 00:42:22,780
 No.

1041
00:42:22,780 --> 00:42:25,580
 Will you know if they're the one in the first month?

1042
00:42:25,580 --> 00:42:27,500
 Likely no.

1043
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:30,140
 So many of us have bought into this formulaic

1044
00:42:30,140 --> 00:42:32,220
 Christian science where we must tell her

1045
00:42:32,220 --> 00:42:35,060
 that I am only pursuing her for the sake of being united

1046
00:42:35,060 --> 00:42:37,300
 to one another in holy matrimony under God

1047
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:38,540
